Benoist
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Leaves sericeous. The long flexuose pedicels are also very distinct. Much more common than the type variety.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
Endemic to Morocco where it usually grows on schists: Central Rif (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Carine et al.</emphasis>
322; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Jury &amp; Shakwa</emphasis>
20997, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Font Quer</emphasis>
358, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Bowring</emphasis>
10) and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Zaïan">Zaian</normalizedToken>
, east of Middle Atlas (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Lynes</emphasis>
153, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Jahandiez</emphasis>
80b, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Davis</emphasis>
557, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gattefossé">Gattefosse</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
s.n. [3/4/1936], 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Maire</emphasis>
s.n. [18/4/1926], 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Sauvage</emphasis>
1359, 8097, 8410).
</paragraph>
